# Diagram Build Specification

This file defines the structural specification for article diagrams. Use draw.io or a compatible editor to construct the diagram according to these rules.

## Layout Structure

### Lanes

The diagram uses a two-lane horizontal layout:

| Lane | Position | Purpose |
|------|----------|---------|
| Control Plane | Top | Routing, configuration, health checking, orchestration |
| Data Plane | Bottom | Request processing, data flow, workload execution |

Each lane is a labeled horizontal container spanning the full diagram width.

### Cell Containers

Within the Data Plane lane, place cell containers labeled A, B, C (extend as needed). Each cell is a rounded rectangle with:

- A bold label in the top-left corner (e.g., "Cell A")
- Internal components representing the cell's stack (compute, storage, queue)
- A solid border indicating the isolation boundary

### Failure Boundary Marker

Use a dashed red rectangle to indicate the failure blast radius. This boundary wraps the affected cell(s) and any shared dependencies within the failure scope. Label it "Failure Boundary" or "Blast Radius."

### Traffic Arrows

- Incoming traffic: solid black arrow from the left, entering the Control Plane lane
- Routing arrows: solid gray arrows from Control Plane to individual cells
- Inter-cell communication (if any): dashed gray arrows between cells
- Failure propagation: dashed red arrows showing failure spread path

### Shared Dependency Box

If the pattern involves shared dependencies (e.g., a global configuration store, shared database), place a labeled rectangle outside the cell containers but within the Data Plane lane. Use a dotted border to indicate it is shared. Connect it to dependent cells with dotted gray lines.

## Labeling Standards

- All components must be labeled
- Labels use sentence case
- Font: sans-serif, minimum 11pt
- No abbreviations unless universally understood (e.g., DNS, LB)

## Spacing Guidance

- Minimum 20px padding inside containers
- Minimum 40px between cell containers
- Minimum 30px between lanes
- Arrows should not overlap labels

## Color Palette

| Element | Color | Hex |
|---------|-------|-----|
| Control Plane background | Light gray | #F5F5F5 |
| Data Plane background | White | #FFFFFF |
| Cell border | Dark gray | #333333 |
| Cell fill | Light blue-gray | #E8EEF2 |
| Failure boundary | Red dashed | #CC0000 |
| Traffic arrows | Black | #000000 |
| Routing arrows | Medium gray | #666666 |
| Shared dependency border | Dotted gray | #999999 |
| Labels | Black | #000000 |

## Notes

- Keep the diagram minimal. Every element must support the article's argument.
- Do not add decorative elements.
- Do not use gradients, shadows, or 3D effects.
- Export to PNG at 2x resolution for clarity.
